               <head>Maimonides' Mishneh torah</head>
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85070287">
                  <summary>The first book of Maimonides' Mishneh Torah, preceded by a large fragment of
              the introduction.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jpr">Hebrew</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="1r" to="143v" />
                     <title xml:lang="en">Mishneh Torah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he">משנה תורה</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>There are short notes on the margin and also between the lines, which contain
                  some different readings and explanations in Persian in Hebrew characters</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="viaf_100185495 http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">Maimonides, Moses, 1135-1204</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="he" key="viaf_100185495 http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">משה בן
                  מימון, 1138-1204</persName>
                     </author>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="1v" to="37r" />
                        <title xml:lang="en">Introduction</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus from="37r" to="143v" />
                        <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-madaʿ</title>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <extent>143 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
                              <height>195</height>
